15. The system of claim 2 and further comprising: 
an element having: 
a base member having a first electrical path and a second electrical path; 
a conductive ring connected to the base member and the first electrical path; 
a biasing member; and 
a conductive plug formed in the conductive ring and biased away from the base member by the biasing member, the conductive plug being connected to the second electrical path.

23. The structure of claim 1 and further comprising: 
a third dielectric support connected to the first metal shield, the third dielectric support having a number of spaced-apart openings; 
a plurality of conductors that contact the third dielectric support such that each conductor is formed across each opening of the third dielectric support; 
a fourth dielectric support connected to the plurality of conductors that are connected to the third dielectric support; and 
a third metal shield that contacts the fourth dielectric support, the third metal shield being spaced apart from the conductors by the thickness of the fourth dielectric support.
